Sentencas: Strontium-substituted lanthanum ferromanganites, La0.8Sr0.2Mn1-yFeyO3+delta (y = 0, 0.2, 0.5, 0.8, 1), LSMF2Y (Y = 10y) for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode applications have been synthetized by a polymeric sol-gel route and deposited on YSZ substrates by a dip-coating process.
Titulo: Lanthanum ferromanganites thin films by sol-gel process.: Influence of the organic/inorganic R ratio on the microstructural properties

Sentencas: The influence of the sol synthesis parameters (metal composition, organic and metal salt concentrations) on the thin film microstructure has been investigated.
Titulo: Lanthanum ferromanganites thin films by sol-gel process.: Influence of the organic/inorganic R ratio on the microstructural properties

Sentencas: In this study, it has been shown that the organic/inorganic ratio, called R, appears as a key parameter to control the microstructural properties of final coatings.
Titulo: Lanthanum ferromanganites thin films by sol-gel process.: Influence of the organic/inorganic R ratio on the microstructural properties
